{"action": "input", "code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    h, w = get_input_dimensions(input_grid)\n    pattern_grid = get_pattern_grid(input_grid)\n    input_grid = cover_columns_with_pattern(input_grid, pattern_grid)\n    return input_grid\ndef get_input_dimensions(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[int, int]:\n    h, w = input_grid.shape[:2]\n    return (h, w)\ndef get_pattern_grid(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    pattern_grid = input_grid[:input_grid.shape[0], :4]\n    return pattern_grid\ndef cover_columns_with_pattern(input_grid: np.ndarray, pattern_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    for j in range(input_grid.shape[1]):\n        input_grid[:, j] = pattern_grid[:, j % 4]\n    return input_grid", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    # Task description: Given a 5x15 image matrix with a black background, your task is to:\n    # Step1: Obtain the height and width of the input image, denoted as h and w.\n    # Step2: Retrieve a h4 portion of the matrix from the top-left corner (0,0) to the bottom-right corner (h-1,3) and label it as pattern_grid.\n    # Step3: Traverse the image matrix by column, assuming the current column number is j, and take out the j%4th column of pattern_grid to cover the current column.\n\n    # Step1\n    (h, w) = `Obtain the height and width of the input image, denoted as h and w.`(input_grid)\n\n    # Step2\n    pattern_grid = `Retrieve a h4 portion of the matrix from the top-left corner (0,0) to the bottom-right corner (h-1,3) and label it as pattern_grid.`(input_grid)\n\n    # Step3\n    input_grid = `Traverse the image matrix by column, assuming the current column number is j, and take out the j%4th column of pattern_grid to cover the current column.`(input_grid,pattern_grid)\n\n    return input_grid\n    ", "gpt_code": "def get_input_dimensions(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[int, int]:\n    h, w = input_grid.shape[:2]\n    return (h, w)\ndef get_pattern_grid(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    pattern_grid = input_grid[:input_grid.shape[0], :4]\n    return pattern_grid\ndef cover_columns_with_pattern(input_grid: np.ndarray, pattern_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    for j in range(input_grid.shape[1]):\n        input_grid[:, j] = pattern_grid[:, j % 4]\n    return input_grid", "holes": {"get_input_dimensions": "Obtain the height and width of the input image, denoted as h and w.", "get_pattern_grid": "Retrieve a h4 portion of the matrix from the top-left corner (0,0) to the bottom-right corner (h-1,3) and label it as pattern_grid.", "cover_columns_with_pattern": "Traverse the image matrix by column, assuming the current column number is j, and take out the j%4th column of pattern_grid to cover the current column."}}
